ing: 2 (7.5 ounce) cans refrigerated buttermilk biscuit dough (such as PillsburyÂ®)
des: "A full recipe of monkey bread is in a BundtÂ® cake pan or mold pan. Cut recipe in half to bake in a smaller metal mold or iron skillet. May be made the night before serving."
ins:
Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
Stir melted butter, parsley, onion, and dill together in a bowl. Dunk biscuit halves into the butter mixture to coat; arrange into a tube-cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven until dough is cooked through and golden brown on top, about 30 minutes.
